   <section id="about" class="reveal section">
  <h2>About the Author</h2>
  <div class="author-bio">
    <p>Dawn Clark's journey to becoming a sci-fi author began with a UFO sighting at age 10 â€“ or was it just a wayward firefly? This spark of cosmic curiosity, combined with a lifelong love for books (ignited by the Trixie Belden series), launched her into the stars of storytelling.</p>
    
    <p>When she's not crafting intergalactic adventures, Dawn can be found decoding the mysteries of her mischievous Jack Russell, Bentley (who she suspects might be an alien in disguise), or stargazing with a notebook in hand, ready to jot down the secrets of the universe â€“ or at least the next plot twist.</p>
    
    <p>The creation of "The Chronicles of the Few" has been an odyssey rivaling her characters' journeys. From lightning strikes of inspiration to navigating creative black holes, Dawn has charted new territories in her imagination. She's even been known to conduct "gravity experiments" (aka tripping over her own feet) in the name of accurate low-gravity scene descriptions.</p>
    
    <p>A self-proclaimed "space detective," Dawn's research has led her down fascinating wormholes, from quantum physics to the perfect recipe for freeze-dried ice cream. She swears her browser history would make even the most seasoned sci-fi fan raise an eyebrow.</p>
    
    <p>When not exploring the cosmos through her writing, Dawn finds joy in the simple things: the laughter of her adorable grandson, the thrill of solving a mystery novel before the last page, and the art of convincing Bentley that the vacuum cleaner is not, in fact, an invading robot.</p>
    
    <p>Dawn is eternally grateful to her readers, whose support fuels her interstellar adventures. Each review is like discovering a new planet in her universe of stories. She's already charting a course for her next sci-fi saga â€“ rumor has it, it might involve time-traveling cats, but you didn't hear that from us!</p>
    
    <p>Ready to embark on a cosmic adventure? Dive deeper into the world of 'The Chronicles of the Few' <a href="sample-chapter.pdf">here</a>. For exclusive updates, behind-the-scenes peeks, and possibly decoded alien transmissions, sign up for Dawn's newsletter <a href="https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLScB37sXKd3AWL6SPKalLuRYu13RLOx34wxEqSnzJytApy8QMw/viewform?embedded=true">here</a>.</p>
